# XUIFramework

Create android UI elements easily, made with kotlin

## Usage

### Easy adapter
```kotlin
val list = arrayListOf(
    TestData("item 1"),
    TestData("item 2"),
    TestData("item 3")
)

recyclerView.adapter =
    XAdapter(R.layout.row_list_test, list) { view, item ->
        //render each item here
        view.setText(R.id.textTitle, item.name)
    }
```

### Easy image using glide
```xml
<--! or you can use GlideImageView -->
<com.tpa.xuiframework.view.GlideImageViewCircle
        android:layout_width="100dp"
        app:url="@{testData.profile}" 
        app:defaultDrawable="@drawable/ic_launcher"
        android:layout_height="100dp"/>

```
[WIKI](https://bitbucket.org/ehsan_hvd/xuiframwork/wiki/Home) for more cool features 

